The specimen is labeled right upper lobe wedge .
Received fresh for frozen section is a 9 x 6.1 x 2.2 cm lung wedge with a 9cm staple line .
The specimen is previously opened and reveals a 2.5 x 2.2 x 1.8 cm white ? tan irregular firm tumor .
The tumor is 0.1 cm to the nearest margin underneath the staple line .
The staple line is removed and the exposed parenchyma is inked black .
Representative sections of the tumor are submitted for frozen section with the remnant put in cassette A91 .
A touch prep is performed ; more cassettes are submitted as follows : A1 through A3 sections of tumor with the nearest margin A4 lung parenchyma underlying the staple line A5 unaffected lung .
B. This specimen is labeled level Xll R. lymph node .
The specimen is received fresh and consists of multiple anthracotic lymph node fragments measuring in aggregate 1.1 x 0.9 x 0.2 cm .
The specimen is entirely submitted in cassette B1 .
C. The specimen is labeled right upper lobe .
Received without ?xative is a 145 g 17.0 x 7.0 x 2.7 cm lobe of lung with stapled bronchial and vascular margins .
There is a 13.5 cm in length stapled line adjacent to the hilum and a 14.0 cm in length stapled line on the opposite side .
A palpable mass is felt and the overlying pleura is inked green .
The staple line adjacent to the pleura is removed and the exposed parenchyma is inked yellow .
The staple line on the opposite side is removed and the exposed parenchyma is inked black .

Sectioning shows a 1.3 x 1.3 x 1.2 cm firm tan mass that grossly abuts the anti-hilar staple line ( black ) and is 0.2 cm subjacent to the overlying pleura ( green ) is 1.0 cm from the hilar staple line ( yellow ) and is 1.5 cm from the bronchial margin .
Additionally there is a 1.0 x 0.9 x 0.7 cm poorly-de?ned hemorrhagic subpleural nodule located greater than 5.0 cm from the bronchial margin and greater than 2.0 cm from both staple lines .
The remainder of the specimen consists of spongy red lung parenchyma without nodules or other lesions .
